WEBVTT

00:18.935 --> 00:21.479
Pirates! They're too strong!

00:23.648 --> 00:24.733
Come on!

00:30.572 --> 00:31.406
Hurry!

00:33.742 --> 00:35.076
Hurry! Hurry!

00:42.333 --> 00:44.127
You lot are pathetic.

00:45.628 --> 00:46.628
You said it.

00:46.629 --> 00:50.383
I knew the East Blue
was supposed to be weak, but sheesh.

00:58.016 --> 01:01.311
Now I've got Marine all over my heels.

01:05.190 --> 01:06.691
This is boring.

01:07.192 --> 01:09.360
What are we doing
in this backwater base anyway?

01:09.944 --> 01:12.447
It's called due diligence, Miss Valentine.

01:13.907 --> 01:14.741
Hmm.

01:17.827 --> 01:19.913
Guard the doors!

01:20.580 --> 01:21.914
Commander Ripper!

01:21.915 --> 01:24.500
Commander Ripper,
the outer perimeter's been breached.

01:24.501 --> 01:25.710
Pirates have entered the base.

01:27.170 --> 01:28.671
Remember your oaths.

01:30.006 --> 01:36.429
To uphold justice,
we will absolutely hold this line.

01:48.441 --> 01:49.317
Hmm.

01:51.111 --> 01:53.196
That's quite a lot of arms you have.

01:55.698 --> 01:56.991
<i>Doce Fleur.</i>

02:10.255 --> 02:11.881
Charge!

02:59.888 --> 03:00.847
Aah!

03:12.108 --> 03:13.651
Where do you keep your dead?

03:18.907 --> 03:20.950
Looks like we need a new Mr. 7.

03:22.952 --> 03:24.078
Or at least a

03:25.038 --> 03:26.164
Mr. Three-and-a-half.

03:28.875 --> 03:31.044
- How disappointing.
- Yeah, which part?

03:31.753 --> 03:33.671
One of our agents biting the dust?

03:34.172 --> 03:35.881
Or the East Blue punk that did it

03:35.882 --> 03:38.342
turning down an invitation
to Baroque Works?

03:38.343 --> 03:40.761
- Both.
- Mr. Zero's not gonna be happy.

03:40.762 --> 03:43.764
No. I can't imagine he will be.

03:43.765 --> 03:45.391
Good thing he's got us.

03:47.310 --> 03:51.147
This is the handiwork of Roronoa Zoro,
is it not?

03:52.315 --> 03:54.067
Bye-bye, darling.

03:54.567 --> 03:55.985
We need to find him.

03:58.738 --> 04:00.990
He… he left.

04:01.574 --> 04:03.533
His captain attacked the base
and freed him.

04:03.534 --> 04:06.411
Then they escaped
and made for the Grand Line.

04:06.412 --> 04:08.581
You telling us
the pirate hunter is a pirate himself?

04:09.165 --> 04:10.250
Awkward.

04:11.334 --> 04:12.377
Who is this captain?

04:23.054 --> 04:25.765
Monkey D. Luffy.

04:29.435 --> 04:30.561
Interesting.

04:31.354 --> 04:32.647
Where is it?

04:34.148 --> 04:35.066
Whoa, rude!

04:35.733 --> 04:37.734
I was using that pepper.

04:37.735 --> 04:40.445
Usopp, you have your tools. I have mine.

04:40.446 --> 04:42.656
You don't see me
grabbing any of your rubber bands

04:42.657 --> 04:44.241
and tossing them into a soufflé.

04:44.242 --> 04:46.618
Yeah, because that would make
a terrible soufflé.

04:46.619 --> 04:48.412
But these new pepper bombs?

04:48.413 --> 04:51.206
The latest and greatest
in Captain Usopp's mighty arsenal.

04:51.207 --> 04:54.876
I hope those bombs of yours are edible
'cause I'm running low on supplies.

04:54.877 --> 04:58.213
Between the way Luffy eats
and whatever it is you do…

04:58.214 --> 04:59.631
Innovative genius?

04:59.632 --> 05:01.967
A miracle I can
keep scrounging meals together.

05:01.968 --> 05:04.386
The kitchen's not the only thing
that's hurting.

05:04.387 --> 05:06.513
We're also low
on ship maintenance supplies,

05:06.514 --> 05:07.431
first-aid supplies.

05:07.432 --> 05:08.766
Sounds expensive.

05:09.642 --> 05:11.436
But necessary.

05:13.062 --> 05:14.480
Better talk to Nami.

05:16.441 --> 05:21.404
Nami, love, for lunch today,
we have a sautéed black pepper octopus.

05:21.904 --> 05:23.530
Thank you, Sanji.

05:23.531 --> 05:26.491
You have octopus. I had egg sandwich.

05:26.492 --> 05:27.617
Mmm.

05:27.618 --> 05:29.661
You have outdone yourself,
as always, Sanji.

05:29.662 --> 05:30.954
I aim to please.

05:30.955 --> 05:34.709
Although, for black pepper octopus,
I don't taste very much pepper.

05:35.752 --> 05:39.421
So I think I have found
our best route into the Grand Line.

05:39.422 --> 05:42.174
We're not too far off,
but there's dangerous traversal ahead.

05:42.175 --> 05:45.761
Looks like this waterway here
cuts right through the Red Line.

05:45.762 --> 05:46.970
I'm not the navigator,

05:46.971 --> 05:50.265
but doesn't this open ocean
seem like a way safer option

05:50.266 --> 05:53.435
than sailing through a mountain?
It connects right to the Grand Line.

05:53.436 --> 05:55.979
Well, good thing
you are not the navigator,

05:55.980 --> 05:57.314
or we would all be screwed.

05:57.315 --> 05:59.149
This is the Calm Belt.

05:59.150 --> 06:01.902
I'm guessing it's not named that
for its easy travel.

06:01.903 --> 06:04.654
No. It is named for its still water
and lack of wind.

06:04.655 --> 06:07.617
You enter the Calm Belt,
and your sails instantly hang limp.

06:08.326 --> 06:09.493
No way to move.

06:09.494 --> 06:11.287
Becalmed and dead in the water.

06:11.788 --> 06:15.332
- Also a breeding ground for sea kings.
- Oh, yeah. Let's not go there.

06:15.333 --> 06:17.250
I killed a bunch of them once.

06:17.251 --> 06:20.129
- We got a lot of bad blood, so it's like…
- Why don't we go to Loguetown?

06:20.797 --> 06:24.424
That sounds like a perfectly safe,
non-dangerous place to visit.

06:24.425 --> 06:25.425
I like this.

06:25.426 --> 06:28.136
Loguetown is the largest Marine hub
in all of the East Blue.

06:28.137 --> 06:31.139
Let's not go there. I changed by mind.
Let's go straight for the Grand Line.

06:31.140 --> 06:33.892
No, there's gotta be
some safer islands around here.

06:33.893 --> 06:35.310
It doesn't seem like it.

06:35.311 --> 06:37.687
We're low on food
and pretty much everything.

06:37.688 --> 06:40.357
This could be our last chance to stock up
before the Grand Line.

06:40.358 --> 06:43.527
It is dangerous
to enter the Grand Line underprepared,

06:43.528 --> 06:45.987
and we're not far away. Maybe we could--

06:45.988 --> 06:48.323
You're free
for the first time in your life.

06:48.324 --> 06:51.660
Haven't you earned the right
to buy yourself a little something nice?

06:51.661 --> 06:53.453
No. No.

06:53.454 --> 06:54.872
Don't you fall for it.

06:56.332 --> 06:57.958
I could do with a little shopping.

06:57.959 --> 06:59.126
- Yeah!
- What?! What?!

06:59.127 --> 07:00.669
Curse you, Sanji! Curse you!

07:00.670 --> 07:04.423
And your charm and your chiseled jawline,
your ocean eyes.

07:04.424 --> 07:07.260
We need someone who can
talk some sense into the… Zoro! Zoro!

07:07.927 --> 07:09.636
Buddy, back me up here.

07:09.637 --> 07:12.055
Sanji and Nami wanna go
to an island full of Marines to shop,

07:12.056 --> 07:15.350
which I think is stupid considering
me and Luffy are on a wanted poster now.

07:15.351 --> 07:16.601
Tell 'em you agree with me.

07:16.602 --> 07:17.478
Hmm.

07:20.022 --> 07:22.150
- Shopping?
- Yeah. Can you believe it?

07:22.859 --> 07:24.985
- Good idea.
- What?!

07:24.986 --> 07:27.112
I need two more swords.
I've been feeling off.

07:27.113 --> 07:29.322
Since the sword-shattering arse-kicking
Mihawk gave you?

07:29.323 --> 07:32.075
- Shut up! You weren't even there.
- I saw what I needed to.

07:32.076 --> 07:34.661
Sorry, Usopp.
That's another vote for Loguetown.

07:34.662 --> 07:37.206
- This isn't over yet. Where's Luffy?
- Where do you think?

07:37.707 --> 07:40.084
Hey, Luffy! Crew meeting.

07:47.175 --> 07:48.468
Coming!

07:52.430 --> 07:54.182
Okay. What's up?

07:54.807 --> 07:56.184
Luffy! Uh…

07:56.684 --> 07:58.852
I've always respected
your position as captain.

07:58.853 --> 08:01.313
Now's time for you to put your foot down
with these hooligans,

08:01.314 --> 08:02.648
otherwise we're gonna get killed.

08:03.858 --> 08:06.401
- What do you mean?
- We need to make a stop.

08:06.402 --> 08:09.154
But we're going to the Grand Line
so I can find the One Piece--

08:09.155 --> 08:10.655
And become King of the Pirates.

08:10.656 --> 08:12.699
And we wanna get there, too, Luffy,

08:12.700 --> 08:15.702
but we need to stop in Loguetown
to get some things first.

08:15.703 --> 08:17.621
- What's in Loguetown?
- Death!

08:17.622 --> 08:19.331
I don't want that.

08:19.332 --> 08:20.957
I need new swords.

08:20.958 --> 08:22.751
Good. That could help with the death.

08:22.752 --> 08:25.171
And we need more food
for the journey ahead.

08:25.671 --> 08:26.588
Even better.

08:26.589 --> 08:27.632
And

08:28.299 --> 08:31.219
it's also the place
where Gold Roger was executed.

08:32.553 --> 08:35.348
The place where the King of the Pirates
was born and died.

08:37.225 --> 08:39.018
Where the legend
of the One Piece was born.

08:40.770 --> 08:42.772
You want to see it, don't you?

08:44.649 --> 08:46.192
You know I do!

08:50.321 --> 08:52.532
And you thought
we were gonna skip Loguetown.

08:58.037 --> 09:01.289
All right, Straw Hats, set course to…

09:01.290 --> 09:03.708
Wait, which way? Okay.

09:03.709 --> 09:06.254
Set course to Loguetown!

10:02.143 --> 10:03.436
Vice Admiral.

10:05.521 --> 10:07.607
I'm sorry about the accommodations.

10:08.190 --> 10:10.234
Not really fit
for the Pirate King, are they?

10:11.027 --> 10:14.322
It wasn't me that came up
with that moniker now, though, was it?

10:15.573 --> 10:17.325
So, Monkey D. Garp.

10:17.992 --> 10:19.993
The hero of God Valley.

10:19.994 --> 10:22.079
The man who captured Gold Roger.

10:22.580 --> 10:24.415
Quite the feathers in your cap.

10:26.626 --> 10:28.251
When's the next parade?

10:28.252 --> 10:29.420
Later today.

10:29.920 --> 10:33.633
And there is a special seat
saved just for you.

10:39.597 --> 10:43.184
Of all the battles
that we've had over the years, Garp,

10:44.143 --> 10:47.355
it's the verbal sparring
that I've always enjoyed the most.

10:48.606 --> 10:49.649
Not me.

10:51.442 --> 10:53.985
It's the beating the piss out of you
up and down the Grand Line,

10:53.986 --> 10:55.071
that was my favorite.

11:14.882 --> 11:15.883
Yeah.

11:19.095 --> 11:21.971
You learn a lot
about what a man's made of in combat.

11:21.972 --> 11:24.265
The clashing of steel.

11:24.266 --> 11:26.727
The feel of his blood
dripping from your knuckles.

11:27.353 --> 11:29.063
Tells you what's in his heart.

11:29.897 --> 11:31.107
In his soul.

11:31.982 --> 11:33.984
We've come to blows many times.

11:36.946 --> 11:39.448
I know you, Garp.

11:40.783 --> 11:42.159
I trust you.

11:44.120 --> 11:46.414
As if you were one of my own crew.

11:49.458 --> 11:51.877
Which is why I have
one final favor to ask.

11:55.965 --> 11:57.049
I have a son.

11:58.634 --> 12:01.846
I need you to find him,
care for him, keep him safe.

12:06.642 --> 12:08.393
Why are you asking this of me?

12:08.394 --> 12:09.979
Because no son

12:10.563 --> 12:12.856
should have to suffer
for the sins of his father.

12:12.857 --> 12:14.608
And what makes you think I'll do this?

12:17.862 --> 12:19.362
Because you're a good man.

12:19.363 --> 12:22.907
A good man
who's about to lead you to the gallows.

12:22.908 --> 12:23.909
True.

12:25.369 --> 12:27.830
But I trust
you won't do the same to my son.

12:29.915 --> 12:32.585
Night may be falling on my time,
but his dawn,

12:33.794 --> 12:35.129
it's only just beginning.

12:38.883 --> 12:40.968
You've cursed me for the last time.

12:52.897 --> 12:54.398
It isn't over, Garp.

12:57.318 --> 12:59.111
Piracy isn't over.

13:00.446 --> 13:01.655
Yes, it is.

13:11.040 --> 13:13.584
Woo-hoo!

13:15.753 --> 13:18.172
Yeah!

13:33.979 --> 13:35.689
Wow, we're really here.

13:36.190 --> 13:37.482
So many people.

13:37.483 --> 13:38.818
Look at this place!

13:43.405 --> 13:44.989
Loguetown.

13:44.990 --> 13:47.576
The town of the beginning and the end.

13:50.162 --> 13:51.831
This is where it all started.

13:52.581 --> 13:54.500
The hunt for the One Piece.

13:55.167 --> 13:57.961
History happened here!

13:57.962 --> 14:00.339
It looks like they're having
some kind of festival.

14:01.340 --> 14:03.217
For Gold Roger's execution.

14:04.343 --> 14:07.262
A festival? Not so good for laying low.

14:07.263 --> 14:11.558
Then we'll just have to be smart.
No attracting unnecessary attention.

14:11.559 --> 14:13.393
I want to see the execution platform.

14:13.394 --> 14:14.812
Of course you do.

14:15.521 --> 14:19.524
Sanji, what if you took Luffy with you
for some food shopping?

14:19.525 --> 14:22.819
- Mmm?
- Food first, then execution platform.

14:22.820 --> 14:25.697
Right! Food will keep him out of trouble.

14:25.698 --> 14:28.157
I am headed to the fashion district.

14:28.158 --> 14:30.619
Zoro, you need new swords, right?

14:31.829 --> 14:33.079
I need money too.

14:33.080 --> 14:34.914
Okay, what do you want me
to do about that?

14:34.915 --> 14:36.165
The cook got money.

14:36.166 --> 14:37.750
I'm buying food for all of us.

14:37.751 --> 14:40.253
- Me having more swords <i>is</i> for all of us.
- Mm-hmm.

14:40.254 --> 14:42.381
God, what I wouldn't give
for another girl on the crew.

14:44.842 --> 14:47.135
You take this, you pay me back.

14:47.136 --> 14:49.013
With 300% interest.

14:49.889 --> 14:50.890
The…

14:51.891 --> 14:54.351
- What if I need more?
- You haggle.

14:55.060 --> 14:57.521
There's a price that they want
and a price that they will take.

15:01.317 --> 15:02.318
Haggle.

15:03.611 --> 15:04.777
Fine.

15:04.778 --> 15:06.863
Let's get our stuff
and get back to the ship.

15:06.864 --> 15:09.532
I'm gonna stay with Nami.
Young woman in the big city.

15:09.533 --> 15:10.743
You gotta keep her safe.

15:11.410 --> 15:12.327
My hero.

15:12.328 --> 15:13.494
Ah.

15:13.495 --> 15:15.330
All right,
we meet back here when we are done,

15:15.331 --> 15:19.375
and remember, this is a large Marine town,
so keep a low…

15:19.376 --> 15:21.586
- Hello, Loguetown!
- Luffy, wait up.

15:21.587 --> 15:22.546
…profile.

15:46.862 --> 15:48.656
What are you standing around for?

15:49.740 --> 15:52.368
- Fish my haul out, will ya?
- Yes, Captain Smoker.

15:54.286 --> 15:57.538
Sir, you… you caught
Koze of the Yes Pirates.

15:57.539 --> 16:00.793
His partner wasn't fortunate enough
to catch a ride back to Loguetown.

16:04.421 --> 16:05.631
Ah.

16:08.050 --> 16:09.760
No pirate escapes me.

16:12.346 --> 16:15.640
- Where the hell's Tashigi?
- Sir, I haven't seen her today.

16:15.641 --> 16:16.767
That girl…

16:18.602 --> 16:23.399
This time of year brings all the wannabe
pirates to Loguetown. We have to be ready.

16:23.899 --> 16:25.526
Throw this scum in the brig.

16:26.026 --> 16:27.361
I'm going on patrol.

16:30.406 --> 16:31.948
Here you go, ladies.

16:31.949 --> 16:35.118
Feels good finally
buying something for myself for once.

16:35.119 --> 16:37.079
Yeah. You sure have bought a lot.

16:37.579 --> 16:39.790
Ignoring that comment
for your own well-being.

16:44.253 --> 16:46.839
I should get something
to conceal my true identity.

16:47.923 --> 16:50.843
Oh yeah. These'll do the trick.

17:17.411 --> 17:18.620
Cool book.

17:19.496 --> 17:20.330
Hmm?

17:24.001 --> 17:25.794
Yeah, it's, um…

17:26.545 --> 17:28.005
It's an Atlas of the East Blue.

17:29.089 --> 17:31.007
I had one just like it when I was a kid.

17:31.008 --> 17:32.134
For a time, anyway.

17:32.718 --> 17:35.470
- You should get it.
- What? No.

17:35.471 --> 17:39.307
No, I'm supposed to be drawing
my own maps. Not using someone else's.

17:39.308 --> 17:42.269
Yeah, but it's something
to remember where you started.

17:43.062 --> 17:45.105
And one day, when you map the world,

17:45.606 --> 17:49.318
you can look back on this one
and see how much better yours is.

17:52.112 --> 17:53.447
You know what? You're right.

17:55.115 --> 17:57.201
It's nice to remember
where we've come from.

17:58.952 --> 18:01.038
You should do something for yourself too.

18:01.538 --> 18:05.584
Something to help you remember home
before we leave it behind.

18:06.460 --> 18:08.961
I didn't really have much growing up.

18:08.962 --> 18:11.048
I don't think
there's something to remember.

18:11.757 --> 18:13.884
Well, maybe not something.

18:14.885 --> 18:16.386
But someone.

18:18.222 --> 18:19.139
Uh…

18:20.724 --> 18:21.725
Ah.

18:47.543 --> 18:48.794
Oh man, oh man, oh man.

18:50.587 --> 18:53.256
- Sorry about that.
- Ah. No, it's my fault.

18:53.257 --> 18:54.675
I'm a bit of a klutz.

18:58.679 --> 19:00.889
Kuina.

19:01.557 --> 19:02.723
What was that?

19:02.724 --> 19:03.851
Nothing.

19:05.394 --> 19:07.312
You just look like someone I used to know.

19:08.230 --> 19:09.648
Well, thank you for your help.

19:10.149 --> 19:13.776
Uh, maybe I could help you in return?
You seem lost.

19:13.777 --> 19:14.903
I'm not lost!

19:15.404 --> 19:17.156
I have a great sense of direction.

19:18.073 --> 19:18.949
Okay.

19:21.743 --> 19:22.619
There.

19:23.829 --> 19:24.872
I'm going there.

19:27.374 --> 19:28.208
Huh.

19:30.002 --> 19:30.961
Was that…

19:32.045 --> 19:33.546
Oh, come on.

19:33.547 --> 19:34.381
Oh, that's it.

19:37.259 --> 19:39.260
Welcome, my young friend.

19:39.261 --> 19:42.055
Uh, how can I serve you on this fine day?

19:42.556 --> 19:43.639
I need new swords.

19:43.640 --> 19:46.392
Of course you do.
Well, you've come to the right shop.

19:46.393 --> 19:49.896
We've got old swords, new swords.
The finest blades in all of the East Blue.

19:49.897 --> 19:53.775
Anything sharp your heart desires
can be purchased right here.

19:56.153 --> 19:57.362
What'll this get me?

19:58.238 --> 19:59.531
Bargain bin's over there.

20:04.077 --> 20:05.370
Friend! Wait.

20:08.624 --> 20:10.334
That sword on your belt, may…

20:12.211 --> 20:13.378
May I see it?

20:16.840 --> 20:17.841
Hmm.

20:31.355 --> 20:32.397
Ah!

20:33.232 --> 20:35.566
No, it's nothing impressive. My mistake.

20:35.567 --> 20:36.568
Sorry.

20:37.653 --> 20:38.528
But…

20:39.655 --> 20:41.572
It's not in terrible condition,

20:41.573 --> 20:45.201
and perhaps I can help you
with your lack of funding.

20:45.202 --> 20:47.870
Say I give you 200,000 berry for it?

20:47.871 --> 20:49.122
It's not for sale.

20:49.623 --> 20:50.748
400,000.

20:50.749 --> 20:51.708
And, uh…

20:52.251 --> 20:54.543
and I'll let you pick
any three swords in the store.

20:54.544 --> 20:57.838
- Is this haggling?
- 750,000, final offer.

20:57.839 --> 21:02.010
Get one top-shelf sword and anything else
you can carry out in the entire store.

21:03.845 --> 21:05.680
I knew I recognized it!

21:05.681 --> 21:07.765
The Wado Ichimonji.

21:07.766 --> 21:11.061
One of the 21 Great Grade blades.

21:17.192 --> 21:19.653
- You really know your swords.
- Kind of my thing.

21:20.320 --> 21:23.407
I never imagined that I'd get
to see one like this in person.

21:24.283 --> 21:26.702
To the right collector,
this would be worth tens of millions.

21:28.745 --> 21:29.579
Hello, Matsu.

21:30.622 --> 21:32.540
Tashigi, my favorite customer.

21:32.541 --> 21:34.042
I'm here to pick up Shigure.

21:34.751 --> 21:37.837
Right, your sword. I'll go get it.
300 berry, please.

21:37.838 --> 21:39.172
It was only 200 last week.

21:39.923 --> 21:41.300
Inflation's a bitch, ain't it?

21:44.803 --> 21:47.096
Ipponmatsu offers
the best sword-sharpening care

21:47.097 --> 21:48.472
if you're ever in need.

21:48.473 --> 21:50.474
I bring Shigure in every week.

21:50.475 --> 21:53.269
Best to leave such important maintenance
to a professional.

21:53.270 --> 21:54.438
Uh…

21:56.273 --> 21:58.442
Hey, since you know so much about swords,

21:59.401 --> 22:00.527
wanna help me pick some?

22:01.361 --> 22:03.280
Absolutely!

22:05.907 --> 22:07.993
Hmm, let's see.

22:08.535 --> 22:11.120
No, you don't want anything in here.

22:11.121 --> 22:14.374
These are duller than feathers, or they'll
shatter before you can swing 'em.

22:15.417 --> 22:20.004
You know, the best swords are more
than just creations for combat, though.

22:20.005 --> 22:22.340
They're pieces of art.

22:22.341 --> 22:23.424
History.

22:23.425 --> 22:27.846
Each one has a story.
A personality. A purpose.

22:28.347 --> 22:29.514
And a price tag.

22:30.432 --> 22:31.767
What is that doing here?

22:33.393 --> 22:34.394
What is it?

22:34.936 --> 22:36.855
That's the Sandai Kitetsu.

22:39.232 --> 22:42.319
- Cool name.
- You… you don't want that sword.

22:42.819 --> 22:43.779
It's cursed.

22:44.279 --> 22:48.282
The Sandai Kitetsu is third in a lineage
of magnificent but ill-fated swords.

22:48.283 --> 22:52.203
Even renowned swordsmen who wield
a Kitetsu blade all meet a tragic end.

22:52.204 --> 22:54.039
Crazy sword girl is right.

22:56.208 --> 22:59.544
Most swordsmen wouldn't dare
use a Kitetsu these days.

23:00.629 --> 23:02.671
I've been wanting
to get rid of that one for years,

23:02.672 --> 23:05.216
but I'm afraid I'll get cursed too.

23:05.217 --> 23:08.053
I am sorry, son,
but I cannot sell that to you.

23:09.596 --> 23:11.473
How about we test what's stronger.

23:12.641 --> 23:13.767
My will,

23:14.309 --> 23:15.685
or the sword's curse?

23:17.396 --> 23:18.522
If I win,

23:20.107 --> 23:21.233
sell it to me.

23:23.485 --> 23:24.569
What are you going to…

23:43.755 --> 23:44.798
I'll take it.

23:54.766 --> 23:55.933
And one more.

23:55.934 --> 23:56.768
Wait.

24:01.982 --> 24:03.150
Wait right there.

24:07.446 --> 24:10.906
Oh, Sanji! I can't believe there's
so much food from the East Blue

24:10.907 --> 24:12.701
that I've never tried before.

24:13.326 --> 24:15.203
I just want to eat it all.

24:15.787 --> 24:20.082
Yeah, no, I get it. It's nice to taste
the flavors from home before we leave,

24:20.083 --> 24:24.880
but think of all the new things we're
gonna try when we get into the Grand Line.

24:25.881 --> 24:28.383
I can't stop thinking about it.

24:30.969 --> 24:32.220
What?

24:32.721 --> 24:34.514
What is this thing?

24:35.056 --> 24:39.436
- That is a blue-finned elephant tuna.
- Yeah.

24:40.020 --> 24:41.770
They're actually native to the South Blue.

24:41.771 --> 24:45.691
Good eye! You really know your stuff.

24:45.692 --> 24:47.986
Well, you know, I've experimented a bit.

24:48.528 --> 24:50.821
He's the best cook in the whole East Blue.

24:50.822 --> 24:54.700
Well, if you want it,
it's yours. It's the last one anyway.

24:54.701 --> 24:57.287
The restaurant Baratie
took almost everything I have.

24:57.871 --> 25:02.709
Adding a new item to their menu.
True blue-fin sauté.

25:03.585 --> 25:05.044
That sounds like the dish you made.

25:05.045 --> 25:06.128
That is the dish I made.

25:06.129 --> 25:08.757
So the old geezer stole it
and put it on the menu.

25:10.050 --> 25:11.885
Sounds like Zeff liked it.

25:12.969 --> 25:14.679
I guess he did.

25:15.347 --> 25:19.350
Well, then, I'm gonna have to keep
impressing him. So I'll take this beauty.

25:19.351 --> 25:20.351
And what else you got?

25:20.352 --> 25:22.229
Follow me.

25:22.729 --> 25:24.314
Luffy, stay here.

25:25.482 --> 25:27.567
<i>And then the whole tower
came crashing down.</i>

25:30.904 --> 25:33.697
Then the village threw a party in my honor
for saving them.

25:33.698 --> 25:37.953
I haven't been gone long, but it's already
some of my craziest adventures yet.

25:39.079 --> 25:41.789
By the time you get this message,

25:41.790 --> 25:43.583
we'll be in the Grand Line.

25:44.543 --> 25:48.672
And… I can't help but be a little…

25:51.007 --> 25:52.133
nervous.

25:53.385 --> 25:56.012
But my crew needs me!

25:56.555 --> 25:59.057
And what kind of captain
would let his people down?

26:00.475 --> 26:03.603
Yeah, honestly, I don't know
what they'd do without me, Kaya.

26:05.105 --> 26:07.232
I'm sure she misses you too, Usopp.

26:09.985 --> 26:11.235
Out of the way, lady.

26:11.236 --> 26:12.445
You lose something?

26:18.076 --> 26:19.910
Give me back my wallet, you thief.

26:19.911 --> 26:22.371
I'd call you one too,
but I don't think it applies.

26:22.372 --> 26:26.792
You don't know what you're talking about.
I run things here in Loguetown.

26:26.793 --> 26:29.753
That's why the streets are so safe.
Can I offer you some friendly advice?

26:29.754 --> 26:30.630
No.

26:33.091 --> 26:34.008
Maybe.

26:34.009 --> 26:35.510
Pick a better mark.

26:36.386 --> 26:39.888
Look for some idiot
who's distracted or lost.

26:39.889 --> 26:41.349
Isolate them.

26:42.434 --> 26:46.937
Lure them in
with the promise of something they want.

26:46.938 --> 26:49.356
Then, when their guard is down,

26:49.357 --> 26:52.152
you take what you want.

26:54.070 --> 26:54.988
Whatever.

26:55.572 --> 26:57.449
I don't need advice from you.

27:00.076 --> 27:01.411
Happy hunting!

27:03.371 --> 27:05.957
- Who was that?
- Just some rookie.

27:08.335 --> 27:09.294
Huh.

27:10.128 --> 27:11.171
What's wrong?

27:11.880 --> 27:13.256
Air pressure changed.

27:13.965 --> 27:15.342
A storm is coming.

27:16.134 --> 27:18.178
What do you mean? I don't feel any rain.

27:19.220 --> 27:20.721
A storm is not just about rain.

27:20.722 --> 27:23.516
There's static in the air.
We need to find the others.

27:25.226 --> 27:26.895
And then get the hell out of here.

27:29.606 --> 27:31.066
That's Yubashiri.

27:33.234 --> 27:36.154
My store may not be much, but, um…

27:46.915 --> 27:48.708
this is the best sword I have.

27:53.797 --> 27:55.089
It's a family heirloom.

27:55.090 --> 27:59.009
Black lacquer tachi sword
with a small clove wild-pattern blade.

27:59.010 --> 28:03.348
One of only 50 Skillful Grade swords
in the world.

28:06.476 --> 28:08.103
I told you I don't have much money.

28:08.603 --> 28:10.355
I'm not asking for money.

28:11.690 --> 28:12.649
Just take it.

28:14.567 --> 28:16.069
And forgive me

28:16.736 --> 28:19.321
for, uh, trying to trick you earlier.

28:19.322 --> 28:20.448
It's, uh…

28:23.410 --> 28:24.911
It's been too long…

28:26.705 --> 28:30.959
since I looked in the eyes
of a worthy swordsman.

28:33.128 --> 28:34.254
And as they say,

28:35.255 --> 28:36.464
a sword

28:37.215 --> 28:39.551
chooses its owner.

28:40.802 --> 28:44.889
And I will pray
for your continued good fortune.

28:59.863 --> 29:02.449
And, uh, thanks for your help.

29:03.074 --> 29:04.325
Hope to meet again someday.

29:05.326 --> 29:06.703
I hope so too.

29:09.080 --> 29:11.541
Hey, look. Look.

29:13.126 --> 29:15.879
Uh, excuse me. I'm looking
for the execution platform.

29:20.300 --> 29:22.676
Do you guys know
where the execution platform is?

29:22.677 --> 29:23.845
Get lost.

29:24.345 --> 29:25.346
Okay.

29:31.311 --> 29:32.686
Wow.

29:32.687 --> 29:36.483
Do you know
where the execution platform is?

29:40.028 --> 29:41.780
It's… it's okay.

29:42.697 --> 29:45.241
I'll come back when you finish your song.

29:46.910 --> 29:48.827
Hello, mark.

29:48.828 --> 29:51.288
I mean, mate.

29:51.289 --> 29:52.206
Huh?

29:52.207 --> 29:56.461
You wouldn't happen to be looking for
Gold Roger's execution platform, would ya?

29:58.213 --> 30:00.005
That is exactly what I'm looking for.

30:00.006 --> 30:04.594
Isn't this your lucky day?
I was just heading in that direction.

30:05.094 --> 30:07.096
Name's Bartolomeo.

30:07.597 --> 30:11.434
And I'm famous around this city for my

30:12.227 --> 30:13.686
hospitality.

30:14.187 --> 30:15.188
Wow.

30:15.688 --> 30:17.105
What's it like being famous?

30:17.106 --> 30:19.858
Oh, I'll tell you all about it.

30:19.859 --> 30:20.860
Wow.

30:39.629 --> 30:40.630
Hmm.

30:44.175 --> 30:45.468
Look! That's it.

30:46.845 --> 30:48.429
The King of the Pirates died over there.

30:49.556 --> 30:51.683
Never gave two shits about the guy.

30:52.308 --> 30:56.645
Marines just make a big deal every year,
trying to remind us of the rules.

30:56.646 --> 30:59.189
Get caught, get dead.

30:59.190 --> 31:01.358
This is where the Great Pirate Era began.

31:01.359 --> 31:04.279
That why
you want to see this place so bad, huh?

31:05.321 --> 31:06.447
Wow.

31:12.287 --> 31:13.788
Everything I've done,

31:14.622 --> 31:15.790
everywhere I go,

31:17.667 --> 31:19.377
it all started here.

31:22.922 --> 31:25.300
I just wanted to see it for myself.

31:35.310 --> 31:37.060
Don't you have a dream you want to follow?

31:37.061 --> 31:38.104
Uh…

31:40.481 --> 31:41.399
Uh…

31:43.484 --> 31:44.319
Uh…

31:44.819 --> 31:47.572
I never thought about that.

31:48.323 --> 31:49.324
Hey!

31:52.994 --> 31:54.287
Huh?

32:00.835 --> 32:02.462
You miss me, dickbag?

32:03.129 --> 32:04.380
Who the hell are you?

32:09.510 --> 32:10.428
Bunny.

32:13.097 --> 32:15.683
It's Buggy!

32:17.310 --> 32:18.477
Hey, that's Buggy.

32:18.478 --> 32:21.396
You know my name,
you stretchy little shitlick.

32:21.397 --> 32:23.523
- I said that.
- It's Bug… It's Buggy the Clown.

32:23.524 --> 32:27.528
That's not what you said.
Oh God, I forgot how annoying you are.

32:29.739 --> 32:31.866
And who is this?

32:32.492 --> 32:34.493
Let me guess. New crew member?

32:34.494 --> 32:39.289
You must be the ship's

32:39.290 --> 32:40.582
stylist?

32:40.583 --> 32:43.168
I wanna make fun of you,
but, honestly, I love what you're doing.

32:43.169 --> 32:46.797
- Sure you wouldn't be better off with us?
- He's famous around here, you know?

32:46.798 --> 32:47.632
His name is--

32:48.800 --> 32:50.426
I'm nobody.

32:50.927 --> 32:56.015
I got nothing to do with him
or you or any other pirate.

32:56.849 --> 33:01.478
- I'm outta here.
- Hey, come on. What's the rush, friend?

33:01.479 --> 33:05.857
You know, I love
a bit of audience participation.

33:05.858 --> 33:07.360
What do you want anyway?

33:08.736 --> 33:10.446
How'd you find me this time?

33:15.493 --> 33:16.786
I knew you'd come here.

33:17.286 --> 33:20.622
Drawn like a shit moth to a shit flame.

33:20.623 --> 33:23.668
But that doesn't ever work out well
for the moth, now, does it?

33:24.335 --> 33:26.628
Oh, I can see it now!

33:26.629 --> 33:29.214
Old Shanksy bouncing you on his knee,

33:29.215 --> 33:33.468
filling your head up with all the stories
of Gold Roger's final curtain call,

33:33.469 --> 33:35.096
dreaming

33:36.472 --> 33:40.142
that one day,
you'd come to stand in his shadow.

33:40.143 --> 33:42.310
Is this another one of your shows?

33:42.311 --> 33:44.272
Oh, no. Tonight's not a show.

33:44.772 --> 33:45.773
Tonight

33:46.649 --> 33:47.775
is a lesson.

33:48.776 --> 33:53.114
And it's where your brief,
pathetic little journey comes to an end.

33:54.323 --> 33:56.451
It's a shame your friends
aren't here to see it.

33:57.952 --> 34:00.038
But lucky for you,

34:01.622 --> 34:03.499
I brought some friends of my own.

34:04.751 --> 34:07.795
Oh, honey bunny!

34:09.338 --> 34:12.467
I am not your honey bunny, clown.

34:15.720 --> 34:16.596
Alvida?

34:20.683 --> 34:22.017
<i>Her</i> name you remember?

34:22.018 --> 34:23.061
You met her once.

34:23.561 --> 34:26.647
I've been thinking about this
for a long time, Straw Hat.

34:27.148 --> 34:28.775
Yeah, it's… it's been a while.

34:29.776 --> 34:30.610
How's your ship?

34:31.527 --> 34:33.904
You lit it on fire.

34:33.905 --> 34:36.031
Right. Whoa.

34:36.032 --> 34:36.990
Whoo.

34:36.991 --> 34:40.952
Anyways, gotta get going, guys.
Grand Line's calling.

34:40.953 --> 34:44.040
Oh, you're not walking out of here alive.

34:49.253 --> 34:50.505
So you want a fight?

34:51.631 --> 34:53.091
Take your best shot.

34:54.175 --> 34:55.051
Okay.

34:56.427 --> 34:58.805
Gum Gum…

35:02.100 --> 35:03.267
Pistol!

35:10.483 --> 35:11.776
How did you do that?

35:12.360 --> 35:14.152
Who the hell are you guys?

35:14.153 --> 35:16.655
She's a real knockout, huh?
I'm pretty lucky.

35:16.656 --> 35:19.407
Same trick won't work twice.

35:19.408 --> 35:20.492
Not anymore.

35:20.493 --> 35:23.120
I ate the Slip Slip Fruit.

35:23.121 --> 35:25.539
Whatever you throw at me slides right off.

35:25.540 --> 35:28.501
I don't care about your devil fruit.

35:29.085 --> 35:30.877
You still can't beat me.

35:30.878 --> 35:32.420
Oh, we'll see about that.

35:32.421 --> 35:35.341
I am Captain Iron Mace Alvida,

35:36.175 --> 35:39.219
the most powerful and ruthless pirate
in the East Blue,

35:39.220 --> 35:41.054
and I will have my vengeance.

35:41.055 --> 35:42.473
Slip Slip Tracks!

35:43.057 --> 35:44.058
Huh?

36:02.618 --> 36:03.870
Aah!

36:04.495 --> 36:06.746
That's our cue!

36:06.747 --> 36:07.789
Take the cuffs up.

36:07.790 --> 36:09.791
All right, make some room, you idiots.

36:09.792 --> 36:11.377
You ain't going anywhere!

36:12.044 --> 36:13.546
I feel

36:14.755 --> 36:16.007
funny.

36:18.926 --> 36:21.386
So woozy.

36:21.387 --> 36:25.140
That's 'cause those new bracelets of yours
are made of seastone.

36:25.141 --> 36:26.434
You ever heard of it?

36:27.476 --> 36:30.605
It's an element
with all the properties of the sea itself.

36:31.105 --> 36:34.232
It saps you
of all your obnoxiously spirited stamina.

36:34.233 --> 36:37.945
And the best part is, it nullifies
your little devil fruit powers.

36:38.905 --> 36:40.113
Just like seawater.

36:40.114 --> 36:43.283
So there's no running away,
and no fighting back.

36:43.284 --> 36:44.952
- Stay with us, pal.
- ...

36:45.745 --> 36:47.955
You don't wanna miss what comes next.

37:01.469 --> 37:05.640
Captain Smoker! Sir, pirates have been
sighted at the execution platform.

37:06.766 --> 37:08.391
Surround the area.

37:08.392 --> 37:10.353
- No one moves till I arrive.
- Yes, sir.

37:10.853 --> 37:12.771
Oh!

37:12.772 --> 37:15.316
Sir, we're so sorry.

37:16.651 --> 37:18.653
Apologize to the captain.

37:20.238 --> 37:21.405
Uh…

37:22.907 --> 37:25.076
Looks like my pants ate your ice cream.

37:26.494 --> 37:28.079
Buy more scoops this time.

37:29.205 --> 37:31.290
Gee, thanks, mister!

37:32.750 --> 37:34.584
Let's go home. Come.

37:34.585 --> 37:36.211
What? Are you waiting for ice cream too?

37:36.212 --> 37:37.755
- Go!
- Yes, Captain Smoker!

37:38.256 --> 37:39.215
Captain!

37:40.675 --> 37:42.092
You're late, petty officer.

37:42.093 --> 37:44.220
- Sorry, sir, I was just--
- I don't care.

37:45.012 --> 37:47.014
You messed up the buttons on your jacket.

37:50.768 --> 37:51.936
Where are we going?

37:52.603 --> 37:53.854
To do our job.

37:58.192 --> 38:00.527
- They're over there.
- Might as well.

38:00.528 --> 38:01.654
Where are they?

38:04.615 --> 38:05.533
Zoro!

38:06.033 --> 38:06.993
Ah.

38:08.619 --> 38:10.246
Oh, you got the swords.

38:10.788 --> 38:11.956
Here's your money.

38:12.498 --> 38:13.541
I didn't need it.

38:14.875 --> 38:17.169
- You didn't kill anyone for those?
- No.

38:18.421 --> 38:19.714
I haggled.

38:20.548 --> 38:21.589
Okay.

38:21.590 --> 38:23.467
Well, you still owe me interest.

38:24.260 --> 38:27.263
Those look like really nice swords.
And someone just gave them to you?

38:30.933 --> 38:31.934
Yeah, pretty much.

38:33.185 --> 38:34.227
Suspicious.

38:34.228 --> 38:36.896
Okay, look, there's a storm coming.

38:36.897 --> 38:39.066
A big one.
We need to get back to the Merry.

38:39.567 --> 38:42.485
- Sanji! You get everything you needed?
- Yes.

38:42.486 --> 38:46.740
I had everything sent to the Merry.
Except this beauty.

38:46.741 --> 38:48.867
She is not leaving my sight.

38:48.868 --> 38:50.161
Where's Luffy?

38:51.537 --> 38:53.331
I thought he would have come back already.

38:53.914 --> 38:55.040
You lost him?

38:55.041 --> 38:57.417
He remembers the fish,
but loses our captain.

38:57.418 --> 38:58.877
Look, we know where he has to be.

38:58.878 --> 39:01.796
If anything happens to him,
you'll be the first I use my new sword--

39:01.797 --> 39:03.089
Stop! Stop! Stop!

39:03.090 --> 39:04.299
We need to find him.

39:04.300 --> 39:07.385
Uh, guys, where's everybody going?

39:07.386 --> 39:08.303
Excuse me.

39:08.304 --> 39:10.013
Pirates at the execution platform.

39:10.014 --> 39:12.641
- They have devil fruit powers.
- Luffy!

39:16.145 --> 39:17.897
My fellow pirates,

39:18.397 --> 39:20.190
citizens of Loguetown,

39:20.191 --> 39:25.571
the charges against this buffoon
known as Monkey D. Luffy are as follows.

39:26.155 --> 39:27.822
He destroyed my ship,

39:27.823 --> 39:30.533
kidnapped my precious Koby,

39:30.534 --> 39:32.411
and turned him against me,

39:32.912 --> 39:36.415
and worst of all, daring to call himself
the future King of the Pirates.

39:37.416 --> 39:40.710
The only justified sentence…

39:40.711 --> 39:41.628
…is death.

39:41.629 --> 39:42.713
Yeah!

39:44.090 --> 39:46.591
Sh, sh, sh, sh, sh!

39:46.592 --> 39:48.594
Sh, sh, sh, sh!

39:49.261 --> 39:50.554
As your lawyer,

39:51.680 --> 39:53.891
I advise that you let me do the talking.

39:59.271 --> 40:00.398
Friends,

40:01.065 --> 40:04.609
good freaks, and residents of Loguetown,

40:04.610 --> 40:06.904
lend me your ears.

40:07.822 --> 40:11.450
Now, is Luffy a stupid little dipshit?

40:12.451 --> 40:13.369
Yeah.

40:14.662 --> 40:17.872
And should we all be deeply humiliated

40:17.873 --> 40:22.377
that he has somehow become
the most wanted pirate in the East Blue?

40:22.378 --> 40:23.461
Of course.

40:23.462 --> 40:24.379
Yeah!

40:24.380 --> 40:28.216
And is he so insufferably obnoxious

40:28.217 --> 40:31.761
that sometimes you just want
to rip that ridiculous hat off his head

40:31.762 --> 40:33.304
and cram it down his throat?

40:33.305 --> 40:34.431
Absolutely.

40:34.432 --> 40:35.391
I know I do.

40:36.517 --> 40:38.059
But even with all that,

40:38.060 --> 40:41.355
does he really deserve to die?

40:43.858 --> 40:45.943
The answer is yes, and I rest my case!

40:48.904 --> 40:51.490
Well, the system works.

40:55.161 --> 40:57.204
You are not a very good lawyer.

40:59.331 --> 41:02.292
Don't you understand the lesson yet, kid?

41:02.293 --> 41:06.588
The most powerful thing in the world
isn't a weapon

41:06.589 --> 41:09.800
or a devil fruit or even a dream.

41:11.552 --> 41:13.888
It's a story.

41:14.388 --> 41:16.055
But all stories end.

41:16.056 --> 41:17.432
Including yours.

41:17.433 --> 41:18.433
Today!

41:18.434 --> 41:19.934
Yeah!

41:19.935 --> 41:23.396
And all of these fine folks

41:23.397 --> 41:25.441
are gonna bear witness.

41:27.526 --> 41:29.444
The boy who would be king

41:29.445 --> 41:30.946
chopped down

41:32.573 --> 41:34.950
before he ever left the East Blue.

41:35.576 --> 41:36.619
Luffy?

41:37.453 --> 41:38.537
Sanji!

41:43.792 --> 41:45.835
Oh, good. The Shit Hats made it.

41:45.836 --> 41:48.671
Take care of the Luff troupe
while I move on with the main event?

41:48.672 --> 41:50.424
Ugh! Out of my way!

41:53.093 --> 41:55.887
So you want to be like
the King of the Pirates, huh?

41:55.888 --> 41:57.640
Well, be careful what you wish for.

42:05.397 --> 42:06.398
Get 'em.

42:14.240 --> 42:15.157
Huh?

42:22.456 --> 42:23.707
At last,

42:24.291 --> 42:26.334
our rematch, Roronoa Zoro.

42:26.335 --> 42:28.128
I don't have time for this.

42:44.061 --> 42:44.895
Hmm.

42:45.396 --> 42:46.230
Nice.

43:06.125 --> 43:07.626
How are you doing that?

43:08.460 --> 43:11.463
I'm slippery from head to toe.
Know when you're beat, little girl.

43:12.464 --> 43:14.008
Nami!

43:20.764 --> 43:23.601
Special attack! Pepper star.

43:35.070 --> 43:36.488
Was that my pepper?

43:36.989 --> 43:39.866
Another round
in Captain Usopp's mighty arsenal.

43:39.867 --> 43:41.577
There he is! Get him!

43:57.468 --> 43:58.635
Should we go in?

43:58.636 --> 43:59.637
No.

44:00.137 --> 44:02.389
Let the pirates tear each other apart.

44:02.890 --> 44:05.100
When they're done,
we'll clean up whoever's left standing.

44:12.024 --> 44:13.399
He's a pirate.

44:13.400 --> 44:16.986
I'll show you
the last thing Gold Roger ever saw,

44:16.987 --> 44:19.197
besides his guts spilling out!

44:19.198 --> 44:20.324
Yeah!

44:25.954 --> 44:28.499
Any last words, Captain Shit-tacular?

44:32.544 --> 44:35.506
My name is Monkey D. Luffy!

44:39.635 --> 44:41.678
I will find the One Piece

44:41.679 --> 44:46.517
and become King of the Pirates!

44:51.105 --> 44:52.106
Let's get him.

45:00.280 --> 45:01.657
Loud!

45:04.076 --> 45:05.994
You don't know

45:06.578 --> 45:09.540
the first thing about being a king.

45:12.251 --> 45:13.794
I know you'll never be one.

45:24.888 --> 45:27.099
Well, heavy is the head
that wears the crown.

45:36.525 --> 45:38.277
So let's take yours off.

45:38.777 --> 45:39.695
Shall we?

45:48.912 --> 45:49.913
Ha!

46:05.471 --> 46:06.471
Zoro!

46:06.472 --> 46:07.472
Sanji!

46:07.473 --> 46:08.514
Usopp!

46:08.515 --> 46:09.349
Nami!

46:12.436 --> 46:13.604
I'm sorry.

46:17.858 --> 46:18.942
I'm dead.

46:21.612 --> 46:22.780
That smile.

46:25.657 --> 46:26.575
Luffy!

46:44.927 --> 46:45.886
That laugh.

46:47.095 --> 46:48.096
Roger.

46:50.808 --> 46:52.267
I'm dead!

46:56.814 --> 46:58.232
Not again!

47:36.603 --> 47:37.688
Lucky me.

47:39.690 --> 47:40.691
All right.

47:41.233 --> 47:42.775
Everyone okay?

47:42.776 --> 47:43.944
Us?

47:45.529 --> 47:47.739
You just got struck by lightning.

47:48.323 --> 47:50.324
Luffy, we need to get back to the ship.

47:50.325 --> 47:51.742
Hold it!

47:51.743 --> 47:54.495
You're all under arrest
by the authority of the Marines.

47:54.496 --> 47:56.874
There's an exit that way.
Get the hell out of here!

47:57.457 --> 47:58.499
Thanks.

47:58.500 --> 47:59.834
My bags!

47:59.835 --> 48:02.212
Do not let those pirates leave this city!

48:05.048 --> 48:08.509
- Sanji would kill me if I left this!
- Wait! Where are Nami and Usopp?

48:08.510 --> 48:10.511
- Did they get lost?
- Nami doesn't get lost.

48:10.512 --> 48:12.139
- Probably at the Merry.
- This way!

48:13.348 --> 48:15.559
- Stop right there.
- Huh?

48:16.059 --> 48:17.185
Or not.

48:19.187 --> 48:20.564
Angry ex?

48:21.064 --> 48:22.315
Get to the ship. I got this.

48:22.316 --> 48:23.233
Hmm.

48:24.735 --> 48:26.361
Should've put it together sooner.

48:26.987 --> 48:28.697
You're Roronoa Zoro.

48:29.281 --> 48:30.949
Bounty hunter turned pirate.

48:31.617 --> 48:34.494
- Then you know you don't wanna do this.
- Oh, I do.

48:35.245 --> 48:37.456
I'm going to take
the Wado Ichimonji from you.

48:40.334 --> 48:42.377
Let's see you try.

49:04.191 --> 49:05.901
You didn't tell me you were a Marine.

49:06.735 --> 49:07.819
You didn't ask.

49:17.079 --> 49:18.788
So the sword geek can fight too.

49:18.789 --> 49:21.124
Better than you. Dropping your elbow.

49:35.722 --> 49:37.014
You're a brute.

49:37.015 --> 49:38.599
No matter how hard you fight,

49:38.600 --> 49:41.561
there will always be
someone better than you with a blade.

49:46.608 --> 49:48.568
I won't surrender this sword for anything.

49:51.154 --> 49:52.906
Especially not you.

49:57.995 --> 49:59.329
Why won't you kill me?

50:05.752 --> 50:07.421
You're no great swordsman.

50:09.089 --> 50:12.050
You're not worthy of the Wado Ichimonji
or any other blade!

50:15.679 --> 50:17.055
Monkey D. Luffy.

50:21.685 --> 50:23.270
I'm Captain Smoker of the Marines.

50:24.187 --> 50:25.480
You're not going anywhere.

50:27.733 --> 50:30.526
Yeah, sorry, Smokey,
but we're kind of in a hurry right now.

50:30.527 --> 50:31.403
I got this.

50:39.202 --> 50:40.579
He has a devil fruit!

50:41.496 --> 50:43.707
Doesn't matter. We take him out.

50:59.598 --> 51:01.933
Gum Gum…

51:04.853 --> 51:06.813
Gatling!

51:37.761 --> 51:38.720
Sanji!

51:43.266 --> 51:45.477
Small fries.

51:46.978 --> 51:49.022
White Blow!

53:11.062 --> 53:14.107
Aah! Aah! Aah!

53:16.651 --> 53:18.277
You're worth 30 million berry.

53:18.278 --> 53:20.280
Aah!

53:27.954 --> 53:29.789
Looks like your luck's run out.

53:39.716 --> 53:42.010
Whose luck did you say?

53:44.721 --> 53:45.721
You.

53:45.722 --> 53:49.016
Who are we to stand in the way
of another man's voyage?

53:49.017 --> 53:51.186
World Government wants your head.

53:51.895 --> 53:53.647
Hmm. Not today.

53:54.272 --> 53:57.067
The world is still waiting for our answer.

54:11.414 --> 54:13.291
Luffy?

54:17.671 --> 54:18.672
Let's go.

54:20.131 --> 54:22.384
Hey. Come on.

54:24.970 --> 54:25.971
Come on.

54:32.811 --> 54:34.228
The hell happened back there?

54:34.229 --> 54:35.521
I'm not sure.

54:35.522 --> 54:38.482
Rain's about to hit.
Zoro, Usopp, drop the sails!

54:38.483 --> 54:40.485
That guy who saved you, who was that?

54:42.279 --> 54:43.446
No idea.

54:54.040 --> 54:55.917
Huh, a pirate, hey?

54:56.418 --> 54:58.878
That's fine if that's
what you have chosen.

55:00.922 --> 55:02.257
Go forth.

55:23.945 --> 55:25.905
Not exactly what you signed up for,

55:26.740 --> 55:27.866
is it, little bird?

55:28.783 --> 55:29.784
Who are you?

55:31.119 --> 55:34.831
Someone who also understands
what it feels like to be kept in a cage.

55:39.961 --> 55:43.214
I gather you're more used to paper cuts
than these kinds of wounds.

55:47.719 --> 55:48.595
Even still,

55:49.804 --> 55:51.764
they must hurt less than your pride.

55:51.765 --> 55:53.558
You don't know what you're talking about.

55:55.769 --> 55:58.188
I know you have potential
that is being squandered.

56:00.065 --> 56:02.984
I know you have skills that are wasted.

56:04.235 --> 56:06.112
Desires that aren't being met.

56:07.197 --> 56:08.531
I know you're strong.

56:09.783 --> 56:11.034
Intelligent.

56:13.078 --> 56:14.162
Beautiful.

56:16.289 --> 56:19.209
This world has so much more
to offer you, little bird.

56:21.127 --> 56:22.712
And you can have all of it.

56:26.800 --> 56:27.884
What's this?

56:29.260 --> 56:30.303
Wings.

56:38.645 --> 56:40.020
Tashigi.

56:40.021 --> 56:41.064
Captain Smoker.

56:41.564 --> 56:42.857
What are you doing here?

56:44.818 --> 56:46.027
Thanks, Raoul.

56:50.365 --> 56:51.366
Mmm.

56:55.912 --> 56:58.415
Gold Roger used to frequent this bar.

56:59.040 --> 57:03.378
They say he even had his final drink here
before he set out into the Grand Line.

57:03.878 --> 57:07.966
After he was captured and killed,
the place kind of lost its draw.

57:08.466 --> 57:09.925
Kill the man,

57:09.926 --> 57:11.386
kill the legend.

57:12.679 --> 57:13.972
So we thought.

57:19.436 --> 57:23.982
I come here every anniversary of his death
to remind myself what I'm fighting for.

57:24.732 --> 57:26.525
What I'm fighting against.

57:26.526 --> 57:28.694
And what is that, sir?

57:28.695 --> 57:30.071
I was there, you know.

57:31.990 --> 57:34.033
The day Gold Roger was executed.

57:34.826 --> 57:37.287
You know what he did
when he faced his end?

57:38.955 --> 57:39.873
He laughed.

57:43.376 --> 57:44.585
I was just a boy,

57:44.586 --> 57:47.755
but even I could see
the effect his words had.

57:48.381 --> 57:51.676
The promise of the One Piece
drove the world into chaos.

57:55.638 --> 57:58.433
No child should have to live
through that kind of madness.

57:59.851 --> 58:01.519
And that's what I'm fighting for.

58:03.188 --> 58:07.192
Dedicated my life to making sure
the world never sees another Gold Roger.

58:12.113 --> 58:12.989
Ah.

58:14.240 --> 58:16.409
Rest up. Tomorrow, we head out.

58:17.327 --> 58:19.077
Head out? To…

58:19.078 --> 58:21.497
- To where?
- The clown spilled the beans.

58:21.498 --> 58:23.833
The Straw Hats
are heading for the Grand Line.

58:26.044 --> 58:27.629
We're gonna hunt 'em down.

58:32.509 --> 58:34.677
He laughed, Tashigi.

58:36.221 --> 58:39.724
Straw Hat Luffy looked death in the face,
and he laughed.

58:40.642 --> 58:43.478
That's what we're fighting against.

59:13.299 --> 59:15.343
Guys! Look!

59:18.846 --> 59:19.931
We made it!

59:20.431 --> 59:21.391
Is that…

59:21.975 --> 59:23.268
Reverse Mountain.

59:23.851 --> 59:25.812
The entrance to the Grand Line.

59:27.397 --> 59:29.482
Our journey gets a lot harder from here.

59:29.983 --> 59:31.275
Harder than Warlords?

59:31.276 --> 59:32.526
Killer sharks?

59:32.527 --> 59:34.696
Whoever that lady with the mace was?

59:35.321 --> 59:36.364
Yeah.

59:37.782 --> 59:39.909
But there's nothing we can't take on

59:40.577 --> 59:41.578
together!

59:42.453 --> 59:43.745
Grand Line,

59:43.746 --> 59:47.499
here we come!

59:47.500 --> 59:50.127
Whoo!

59:50.128 --> 59:54.132
Yahoo!

59:55.258 --> 59:57.594
Yeah!
